🌟 1. The Brave Little Cloud

High in the sky lived a small cloud named Puffy. Unlike the big clouds, Puffy was tiny and often ignored. The larger clouds would say, “You’re too small to do anything important.”

One day, the sun was shining very bright, and the land below became dry. Rivers started shrinking, and plants began to droop. Puffy looked down and felt sad. “I wish I could help,” he said.

The big clouds laughed. “You? You don’t even have enough water!”

But Puffy decided to try. He gathered all the tiny drops he had and slowly floated over a small village. With all his strength, he let out soft, gentle rain.

Below, a small plant drank the water and stood up again. Birds chirped happily, and children ran outside to enjoy the drizzle.

Seeing this, the big clouds realized something important. Even a little cloud could make a big difference.

From that day on, they respected Puffy. And Puffy learned that you don’t need to be big to be important.

Moral: Even small efforts can create big changes.